Key Match Events: Travis Jankowski robbed Andrew Vaughn of a walk-off three-run homer in the ninth inning, securing the Rangers' 4-3 win over the White Sox.
Wyatt Langford hit a three-run home run in the fourth inning for the Rangers.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Bruce Bochy expressed excitement about Jankowski's game-saving catch.
Andrew Chafin, the pitcher, acknowledged Jankowski's play and jokingly mentioned owing him a few steak dinners.
Travis Jankowski reflected on the significance of his catch, calling it a once-in-a-lifetime play.
Andrew Vaughn praised Jankowski's catch, acknowledging the effort and skill involved.
